    <h1>An Act to establish a national strategy for eye care</h1>
    <p><strong>Bill Number:</strong> C-284</p>
    <p><strong>Current Status:</strong> National Strategy for Eye Care Act</p>
    <p><strong>Last Major Stage Completed:</strong> At second reading in the Senate</p>
    <p><strong>Parliament Session:</strong> 44th Parliament, 1st session</p>

    <h2>Readings</h2>
    <h3>Senate Readings:</h3>
    <ul>
        <li>First - Completed</li>
        <li>Second - Not Completed</li>
        <li>Third - Not Completed</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>House Readings:</h3>
    <ul>
        <li>First - Completed</li>
        <li>Second - Completed</li>
        <li>Third - Completed</li>
    </ul>

    <p><strong>Royal Assent:</strong> Not Completed</p>
    <p><strong>Sponsor:</strong> Hon. Judy A. Sgro (Humber River—Black Creek)</p>
    <p><strong>Bill Type:</strong> Private Member’s Bill</p>

    <h2>Bill Content Summary</h2>
    <p>This enactment provides for the development of a national strategy to support the prevention and treatment of eye disease, as well as vision rehabilitation, to ensure better health outcomes for Canadians.</p>
    <p>It also designates the month of February as <strong>“Age-Related Macular Degeneration Awareness Month”</strong>.</p>

    <h2>Contact Information</h2>
