    <h1>An Act to amend the Competition Act (efficiencies defence)</h1>
    <h2>Bill Number: C-339</h2>

    <div class="status">
        <strong>Current Status:</strong> Bill not proceeded with<br>
        <strong>Last Major Stage Completed:</strong> First reading in the House of Commons<br>
        <strong>Parliament Session:</strong> 44th Parliament, 1st session<br>
        <strong>Senate Readings:</strong> First - Not Completed, Second - Not Completed, Third - Not Completed<br>
        <strong>House Readings:</strong> First - Completed, Second - Not Completed, Third - Not Completed<br>
        <strong>Royal Assent:</strong> Not Completed<br>
        <strong>Sponsor:</strong> Ryan Williams (Bay of Quinte)<br>
        <strong>Bill Type:</strong> Private Member’s Bill
    </div>

    <h2>Bill Overview</h2>
    <p>This enactment amends the Competition Act to repeal the provision of the Act setting out the <strong>“efficiencies defence”</strong>. This provision prevents the Competition Tribunal from making an order against any party to a merger or proposed merger if the Tribunal finds that the merger or proposed merger has resulted in, or is likely to result in, gains in efficiency that will exceed the adverse effects of any prevention or lessening of competition.</p>

    <h2>First Reading</h2>
    <p><strong>Date:</strong> June 8, 2023</p>
    <p><strong>Sponsor:</strong> Mr. Williams</p>

